Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 of Mammography/Breast ultrasound
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Intramammary lymph node' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Right' checkbox
Then 'Short axis diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Longitudinal axis diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Disturbed internal architecture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased vascularization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsular infiltration' checkbox is enabled
And '> 1 lesion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Disturbed internal architecture' checkbox
Then 'Hilar obliteration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Irregular cortical width' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Left' checkbox
Then 'Short axis diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Longitudinal axis diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Disturbed internal architecture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased vascularization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsular infiltration' checkbox is enabled
And '> 1 lesion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Disturbed internal architecture' checkbox
Then 'Hilar obliteration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Irregular cortical width' checkbox is enabled
